5..Compile and Execute the C program to change all the digits of a number to bring the digit at the 
last position to the first position and vice-versa using loop. Get the input from user.
Sample Input:
Number: 14567
Sample Output:
Reverse Number: 76541
Test cases:
1. -45721
2. 000
3. AD1947
4. !@#$%
5. 145*999=144855
#include <stdio.h>
int main(){
 int Num, rev_Num = 0, remainder;
 printf("Enter the number to reverse: ");
 scanf("%d", &Num); 
 while (Num != 0){
 remainder = Num % 10;
 rev_Num = rev_Num * 10 + remainder;
 Num = Num/10;
 } 
 printf("The reversed number is: %d", rev_Num);
return 0;
}
Testcases:
1.Enter the number to reverse: -45721
 The reversed number is: -12754
2. Enter the number to reverse: 000
 The reversed number is: 0 
3.Enter the number to reverse: !@#$%
 The reversed number is:%$#@!
4.enter the number to reverse: 145*999=144855
 The reversed number is :558441=999*541
5.enter the number to reverse :AD1947
 The reversed number is :7491DA
